# Line-ending policy. Shell scripts and Dockerfiles run inside Linux containers,
# so they MUST be LF — a Windows checkout (core.autocrlf=true) would otherwise
# ship CRLF, and a `#!/bin/sh\r` shebang makes the kernel exec `/bin/sh\r`
# -> "exec ...: no such file or directory" at container start.
*.sh        text eol=lf
Dockerfile* text eol=lf

# Binary fixtures must never be line-ending-normalized.
*.pptx      binary
